hint.content:
First, we use the two points to find the slope:

$\begin{align}
\text{Slope}&=\dfrac{1-5}{7-3}
\\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4}{4}
\\\\
&=\maroonC{-1}
\end{align}$

Now we use one of the points, let's take $(\blueD 3,\greenD 5)$, and write the equation in point-slope:

$y-\greenD 5=\maroonC{-1}(x-\blueD{3})$
